        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2020-10-08 21:21:04.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1: Code-Review-2\n> \n> You don't need that.. as I updated docs\n> \n> simply run: mvn clean install -Pdocker -Pdocker.skip.push=true\n> \n> Above will create docker image but will not push to any docker-repo\n\n@Kapil\nshall you double check this command for generating docker images \nAnd -Pdocker.skip.push=true isn't a profile \n \"[WARNING] The requested profile \"docker.skip.push=true\" could not be activated because it does not exist.\"",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "a00a83a270412d31e78e7f86169bb0f177efbef3",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 865,
          "name": "KAPIL SINGAL",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "ks220y@att.com",
          "username": "ks220y"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2020-10-13 16:05:41.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1:\n> \n> > Patch Set 1: Code-Review-2\n> > \n> > You don't need that.. as I updated docs\n> > \n> > simply run: mvn clean install -Pdocker -Pdocker.skip.push=true\n> > \n> > Above will create docker image but will not push to any docker-repo\n> \n> @Kapil\n> shall you double check this command for generating docker images \n> And -Pdocker.skip.push=true isn't a profile \n>  \"[WARNING] The requested profile \"docker.skip.push=true\" could not be activated because it does not exist.\"\n\nMy bad, I meant to add another mvn argument not profile: -Ddocker.skip.push=true\n\nAnother thing, we can remove <docker.push.phase> and related use from all poms, that is not required anymore !\n\nAs adding another execution makes docker-maven-plugin to build docker image twice if phase is deploy (and that's where jenkins was taking much longer than usual)",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
